North Platte Public Schools is now taking applications for Substitute Teachers for the 2020-2021 school year.
Apply online at www.nppsd.org

SUBSTITUTE TEACHER

For the 2020-2021 School Year

Substitute teachers are those who hold a bachelor degree (or higher) in education
Requires teaching or substitute certificate
Applicants who do NOT hold a degree in education, must apply for the Certified Teacher, Local Substitute through NDE information is available on their website at https://www.education.ne.gov/tcert/

To complete the on-line application for Substitute Teacher:

Include email addresses for a minimum of three references
Upload a copy of your transcripts
Upload a copy your teaching certificate*

text:
North Platte Public Schools is now taking applications for Substitute Teachers for the 2020-2021 school year.
Apply online at www.nppsd.org

SUBSTITUTE TEACHER

For the 2020-2021 School Year

Substitute teachers are those who hold a bachelor degree (or higher) in education
Requires teaching or substitute certificate
Applicants who do NOT hold a degree in education, must apply for the Certified Teacher, Local Substitute through NDE information is available on their website at https://www.education.ne.gov/tcert/

To complete the on-line application for Substitute Teacher:

Include email addresses for a minimum of three references
Upload a copy of your transcripts
Upload a copy your teaching certificate*

*Applicants that are hired will be required to provide official transcripts and a valid Nebraska Teaching Certificate to Human Resources prior to starting to work. Applicants must schedule an HR interview and attend Orientation before being placed in substitute pool.

UPDATED - Drive Through Backpack Pickup Friday, May 29th
NPPSD is providing free pre-packed food packs to NPPSD children 18 years old and younger.
Every-Other Friday beginning, until further notice
Drive Through Location McKinley Education Center

Packs will be provided in pre-packaged bags for all district children ages 18 and younger every-other Friday until further notice.
Enter from F street and circle in front of the McKinley Education Center. Stop at the designated area, pick up your pack, then exit by turning left on Sycamore.
Please do not park and/ or get out of your vehicle.
Please do not congregate or consume meals on-site.

The distribution will be from 8:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. or until all packs are gone.

Stone Named North Platte Public Schools Foundation Scholarship Recipient
The North Platte Public Schools Foundation is pleased to announce that it has awarded a $500 North Platte
Public Schools Foundation Scholarship to 2020 NPHS graduate Clay Stone. Clay is the son of John and Jessica
Stone.
Clay plans to attend the University of Nebraska-Lincoln to pursue a degree in elementary education. He enjoys
serving students at camps and church and plans to pursue a degree working with youth. Clay has enough
college credits to fill a whole school year thanks to dual credits from Mid Plains Community College. Clay
wishes to obtain a Masterâ€™s degree in either school administration or divinity. His goal is to become an
administrator or a youth pastor. An honor student, Clay was involved in Journalism, Tennis, Soccer and
Bowling. He was also a member of the homecoming court his senior year.

For more information, contact the North Platte Public Schools Foundation at 696-3325.
